{{Primary sources|date=August 2009}} {{Infobox recurring event |name = Arizona Renaissance Festival |image = Arizona Renaissance Festival.jpg |alt = |caption = Jousting tournament at Arizona Renaissance Festival, March 2014 |location = [[Gold Canyon, Arizona|Gold Canyon]], [[Arizona]] |genre = Renaissance fair |first = 1989 |dates = Late winter to mid spring |attendance = 250,000 (average) |area = {{convert|30|acre|m2}} |free_label = Stages |free_text = 14 |website = {{url|http://www.arizona.renfestinfo.com/}} }} The '''Arizona Renaissance Festival''' is a Renaissance-themed [[amusement park]] and [[Renaissance fair]] in [[Arizona]] located in [[Apache Junction, Arizona|Apache Junction]] east of the [[Phoenix metropolitan area|Phoenix metro area]] near [[Gold Camp, Arizona|Gold Canyon]]. The Renaissance Festival usually runs from late winter to mid spring every year, as the winters and springs in the area are actually very mild and pleasant. The Festival is open Saturdays, Sundays, and President's Day Monday.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.visitarizona.com/events/fairs-and-festivals/31st-annual-arizona-renaissance-festival|title=|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004021229/https://www.visitarizona.com/events/fairs-and-festivals/31st-annual-arizona-renaissance-festival|archive-date=2018-10-04|dead-url=no|access-date=|df=}}</ref>
==General information== The Festival is reminiscent of a 16th century European village<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.visitphoenix.com/event/arizona-renaissance-festival/102994/|title=Visit Phoenix AZ Renaissance Festival|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181004021154/https://www.visitphoenix.com/event/arizona-renaissance-festival/102994/|archive-date=2018-10-04|dead-url=no|access-date=|df=}}</ref>. The fairgrounds feature a 14-stage [[theater]], a {{convert|30|acre|m2|adj=on}} [[circus]], regularly scheduled [[jousting]] tournaments and a feast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://emol.org/azrenfest/index.html|title=What's New at the Arizona Renaissance Festival 2019|website=emol.org|access-date=2007-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070225024611/http://emol.org/azrenfest/index.html|archive-date=2007-02-25|dead-url=no|df=}}</ref> Also provided is the Artisan Marketplace, an outdoor arts and crafts market located throughout the park in which merchants from around the nation sell many different kinds of hand-made or period-themed goods.
Other staples of the park include a petting zoo, several live performances, and a selection of food such as 'steak on a stake', sausages, turkey legs, and others. Patrons are welcome to wear costumes and costumes are available to rent at the festival.
