The '''Belleayre Music Festival''' is an annual festival in the [[Catskill Mountains]] of [[Upstate New York]]. Founded in [[Highmount]], NY, Phyllis and Mel Litoff, raised the prominence of the festival after becoming co-artistic directors in 1993.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2002/07/29/nyregion/phyllis-litoff-63-music-festival-director.html?pagewanted=1 Phyllis Litoff, 63, Music Festival Director - New York Times<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Since then, the festival has hosted such artists as James Blunt, Rosanne Cash, Branford Marsalis, [[Frankie Valli]],<ref>''Big Names, Big Shows, Big Nights'', The New York Times, May 14, 2006.</ref> Obie Benson,<ref>''Obie Benson, 69, the Original Bass Voice of the Four Tops'', The New York Times, July 2, 2005</ref> Lyle Lovett, The Neville Brothers,<ref>''Lovett, Neville Brothers head Belleayre lineup''. The Times Union (Albany, NY) April 17, 2004</ref> Linda Eder, Ray Charles, and Wynton Marsalis.<ref>''Ray Charles, Wynton Marsalis, Linda Eder Lead Belleayre Festival''. Season Internet Wire April 1, 2003.</ref>
