The '''Kannur Kotta rape case''' refers to the gang rape of a married Muslim woman by her husband along with his friends at the [[St. Angelo Fort|Kannur Fort]] in the year 1993. The case was landmark event in the history of [[Kerala]] with woman rights activists organising a ''Kitchen bandh'' and a sustained campaign to bring the guilty to justice. The husband Ibrahim and his four friends were convicted and imprisoned for 7 years, and ordered to pay Rs 50,000 each as restitution to the victim.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/lifestyle/a-22-year-old-kitchen-bandh-and-victory-for-a-rape-survivor |title=A 22-Year-Old ‘Kitchen Bandh’ and Victory for a Rape Survivor |publisher=The Quint |date= |accessdate=2018-01-26}}</ref>

