|bgcolor=lightgreen|[[File:Flag of Reformed Government of the Republic of China.svg|150px]]
|bgcolor=lightgreen|[[Jiangsu]], [[Zhejiang]], [[Anhui]], [[Nanjing]], and [[Shanghai]], [[Nationalist Government (China)|China]]
|bgcolor=lightgreen|The Reformed Government of the Republic of China (RGRC) was created in Nanking, after the [[Battle of Nanking]] on 28 March 1938.<ref>{{cite book|last=Ristaino|first=Marcia R.|title=The Jacquinot Safe Zone: Wartime Refugees in Shanghai|date=2008|publisher=Stanford University Press|isbn=0804757933|page=93|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MbeT3r-bAfUC&pg=PA93&dq=Reformed+Government+of+the+Republic+of+China&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pz59U_yBI9PJsATWyIGoAg&ved=0CFIQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>  The RGRC was made to have the appearance to legitimacy, and had [[Wang Jingwei]] as the first Chairman of the RGRC.<ref>{{cite book|last=Ienaga|first=Saburo|title=Pacific War, 1931-1945|date=2010|publisher=Random House LLC|isbn=0307756092|page=170|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=49bWRrBQP74C&pg=PA170&dq=Reformed+Government+of+the+Republic+of+China+nanking&hl=en&sa=X&ei=l0B9U5S8ErKqsQSSsYHgBg&ved=0CEIQ6AEwBA#v=onepage&q&f=false}}</ref>  Despite this, the government was filled with "nonentities who posed no threat to the Japanese exercise of real power."  It was merged into the [[Reorganized National Government of China]] in 1940.<ref>{{cite book|last=Willmott|first=H. P.|title=The Great Crusade|date=2008|publisher=Potomac Books, Inc.|isbn=1612343872|page=159|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5L-bwPZK7PQC&q=reformed+government#v=snippet&q=reformed%20government&f=false}}</ref>
